task.summary: Added a trainServices factory service to list the stations.
The stations service now makes the $http call to the restful web service /api/stations url. Stations sorted in name order.
Can now add a station to the database from the web application.
Storing stops as times and keeping them sorted
Updating origination and termination stations based on stops array
Updated the train description with a nicely formatted time and the translation of the termination station.

Change train numbers to ints. Remove the new train page and simply assign the next number for the new train. The train stops define the train description, origination and termination stations anyway so there is no need to prompt for this when a new train is created.
Created directive to give back the focus to the stop time
First attempt at an up time directive.
Directive works better interacting with scope variables rather than the controls.
hpCopyTime now works with isolate scope
No longer call back to the server to display the station name after an add. Rather use the filter cache.
Show the trains for a station
Show the stop time for each train for the displayed station
Make the trains sort by time for a station
Implement cache and helper services to assist with train stop validation.
Show the station lines in the train stop list via a new filter.
Don't allow a station to be deleted if it is a stop on a train.
Building fitlers for finding trains by start and stop station
Allow the station filters to function singlely
Allow navigation from station list to a filtered train list
Show a tooltip on the stop count
Filter the start and end station drop downs so that if one is selected the other only shows choices where connections are possible.
Show elapsed time until train arrival
Properly killing the timer when the scope is destroyed
Created directive to show elapsed time
Add CSS styling to elapsed directive.
Use the new elapsed directive in the trains page
Add a dropdown to the stations list to select a destination
hp-station-select is creating the correct stations for the select HTML element.
Created a dialog for duplicating a train
Put in multiple train select and a delete trains function.
Refresh train page after deleting train(s)
First attempt at moving the focus on the click events for the station movement in a line.
Playing around with different types of station selection.
Added a section to play with d3
Fixed up the dropdown menu and added the use of the d3 scale object.
Add rotated labels along the X axis.
